name: Community Ecology
description: Nature and analysis of community structure; disturbance and community development; species interactions; community assembly processes. Computer exercises in weekly labs provide training in sampling, simulation, and data analysis.
prerequisites: BIO220H1; and a course in statistics from EEB225H1 (recommended),PSY201H1, STA220H1/STA250H1/STA257H1/STA288H1, GGR270H1, HMB325H1
